* Introduction

This is my Emacs configuration with various collected lisps.

All the files should be placed in "~/.emacs.d/", where "~" means your
HOME. For Windows users, please set a environment vairable for your
account.

* Installation

1. Clone the repository to "~/.emacs.d/".

2. Enter "~/.emacs.d/backup/" folder, and decompress 

     - `elpa.tar.gz':      lisps downloaded via Emacs ELPA package
                           services, which is shipped by Emacs 24.1
                           or later (`package.el'). 
     - `emacswiki.tar.gz': lisps download from emacswiki.org via
                           `auto-install.el' functions.
     - `lisps.tar.gz':     manually downloaded lisps and git 
                           submodules.

   to the  "~/.emacs.d/" folder.
   
     - `cedet-8112.tar.gz'

   to the  "~/.emacs.d/lisps/" folder

3. Enter the "~/.emacs.d/lisp/cedet" folder, and run

     "Emacs -nw -Q -l cedet-build.el -f cedet-build"

   in terminal/command-line to install the cedet package.

4. Run Emacs, you will get errors, but it is OK.

5. "M-x xy/emacs-build" serveral times to build the whole customized
   emacs, untill there is no error.

6. Restart Emacs.

* Tips

** Customize configurations

After installation, you may want to customize the configuration files
in "~/.emacs.d/my-lisps/init/". Just do it and save your files.

If you made changes to

- `~/.emacs.d/my-lisps/init/xy-rcroot-env.el'
- `~/.emacs.d/my-lisps/init/xy-rc-utils.el'

don't forget to delete the their compiled elc files, before your
rebuild, or you will got errors in Windows.

** Change local lisp packages

After you update/delete/modify the local lisp packages, just
change the corresponding configuration files and run 
"M-x xy/emacs-build" in the Emacs program to activate the new 
lisps.

